#raptok #music #reels #reelsinstagram #rnb #rap #rnbmusic #rnbsoul #brockhampton

My (personal) top 5 performers of all-time🔥🔥🔥

I’ve seen a lot of people perform. Honestly everyone major except Drake and Future and I narrowed down my top 5 based on personal experiences. Read below👇🏾:

5. @kendricklamar was my FIRST concert ever so this performance holds a special place in my heart❤️‍🔥. I was like 15 or 16 and what I really remember was his ability to keep the same energy throughout the entire concert. Plus the production was INSANE. Just me and my boys turning up to DAMN😭 an amazing first concert!

4. @dontoliver I have seen Don TWICE now🔥 and I’ll continue to see him. Pretty unreal I was this close to him😭 but his Hardstone Psycho tour was also mentally INSANE🤯 The production + he would freestyle songs at the end. Don is truly a must see😮‍💨

3. @realcoleworld J.Cole is my goat and he is 3 on this list because of how REAL and authentic he is when he performs. Outside of his remarkable rap performances, he truly TRULY speaks to the audience and it felt like he was helping everyone in that crowd get through the BS of life. Spiritual experience ❤️‍🔥

2. @playboicarti I saw Carti at RL NYC 2021 and to this day, it’s the BEST concert I’ve ever been to🔥 I’m a real rager so to be in that moment was amazing + the rain and overall production of his set. Not everyone can enjoy a Carti concert but it’s a night I’ll NEVER be able to forget 🧛🏿‍♂️

1. @travisscott last but not least is Trav🔥🔥🔥 he’s the BEST performer of our generation by a mile. I’ve seen him twice now and he never fails to provide the most INSANE concert experiences a human could possibly have. I’ve been in the pits at trav concerts and I’ve been in seats and I had a fye time in both🔥 when it’s all said and done Trav will be the GOAT performer❤️‍🔥
Just remember😭

5 rappers who rap better than your favorite rapper🔥

We all know that some of the biggest rappers right now are not the best at actually rapping. There are a bunch of rappers HOOPING rn. But here’s 5 of my favorites:

5. @mickjenkins is one the best rappers out that’s actually HOOPING🔥Mick has been around for a while but ‘The Patience’ was one of my favorite rap albums in the last 3 years

4. @smino wordplay genius. I would say 2017-2019 Smino was my favorite rapper. He’s not underrated but very undervalued🔥 Him and Monty created an entire new sound sonically

3. @erickthearchitect is more than just a rapper, he’s a true artist. The Flatbush zombies to this day are still my favorite rap group ever and Erick was always the center point to me for that group🔥

2. @joeybadass is the best rapper out that is still not recognized by the mass majority of people. Has been the best rapper out of NY for awhile🔥 and being from the NJ/NY area I view him in the convos with Nas, Biggie, and Jay when it comes to vocal delivery, debut albums, and lyrics

1. @jidsv self explanatory, there is really no one touching JID at this current moment. Hands down a top 5 hooper in today’s rap game. A true artist/story teller/and overall rapper. JID has all the elements to be an iconic rapper in history (voice, bars, flow) and to me he’s a top 3 rapper out right now!🔥

I thank God everyday that I’m able to listen to music like this😭❤️‍🔥

LAUNCH DAY🚀 Hats Officially Dropped🖤

If you signed up on the waitlist, use the special discount that was sent to your email🔥 (expires in 24 hours)

Hats are VERY limited so get yours before they sell out❤️‍🔥

Story Time📜: How These Hats Were Made…

I knew I wanted to make trucker hats for the summer but didn’t have the knowledge or software on how to cook them up🔥

I wanted to express my feelings through the clothes so I hit up @nickyontheweb to help me out with the design process…

There was a specific font that I wanted and Nick was able to cook up and find the font for me but the font and text alone wasn’t enough for what my vision was…

One of my main DBA’s (digital brand assets) is a globe, specifically a wireframe globe, so I knew I needed that element on the hats somewhere….

Nick was able to cook up the design with the globe which we then used as the patch for outside and inside the hat. I wanted it to be brand specific and I think we were able to accomplish that with this design…

The brand lining on the inside was just another cherry on top to stay up to par with major brands (Mitchell & Ness, Nike, Etc.)

At the end of the day, I put in countless hours editing and discussing with manufacturers to make my clothes as high quality as possible. And with the help of Nick and my manufacturer we were able to do that🖤

If you stuck around this far… comment “🔥” all I’ll give you a special discount you can use and if you fw them, I appreciate the support and love❤️‍🔥
